[{"text": "I'm a savant,", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or more precisely,", "start": 17.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a high-functioning", "start": 19.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "autistic savant.", "start": 21.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a rare condition.", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And rarer still when accompanied,", "start": 25.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as in my case,", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by self-awareness", "start": 30.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and a mastery of language.", "start": 32.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Very often when I meet someone", "start": 35.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they learn this about me,", "start": 38.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there's a certain kind of awkwardness.", "start": 40.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I can see it in their eyes.", "start": 43.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They want to ask me something.", "start": 46.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in the end, quite often,", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the urge is stronger than they are", "start": 51.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they blurt it out:", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"If I give you my date of birth,", "start": 56.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can you tell me what day of the week I was born on?\"", "start": 58.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 60.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Or they mention cube roots", "start": 63.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or ask me to recite a long number or long text.", "start": 66.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I hope you'll forgive me", "start": 70.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if I don't perform", "start": 72.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a kind of one-man savant show for you today.", "start": 75.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I'm going to talk instead", "start": 79.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about something", "start": 82.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "far more interesting", "start": 84.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than dates of birth or cube roots --", "start": 86.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a little deeper", "start": 89.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and a lot closer, to my mind, than work.", "start": 91.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I want to talk to you briefly", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about perception.", "start": 96.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "When he was writing the plays and the short stories", "start": 99.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that would make his name,", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Anton Chekhov kept a notebook", "start": 104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in which he noted down", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "his observations", "start": 109.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the world around him --", "start": 111.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "little details", "start": 113.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that other people seem to miss.", "start": 115.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Every time I read Chekhov", "start": 118.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and his unique vision of human life,", "start": 121.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I'm reminded of why I too", "start": 125.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "became a writer.", "start": 127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In my books,", "start": 129.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I explore the nature of perception", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and how different kinds of perceiving", "start": 133.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "create different kinds of knowing", "start": 136.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and understanding.", "start": 138.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here are three questions", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "drawn from my work.", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Rather than try to figure them out,", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'm going to ask you to consider for a moment", "start": 149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the intuitions", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the gut instincts", "start": 154.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that are going through your head and your heart", "start": 156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as you look at them.", "start": 158.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For example, the calculation:", "start": 161.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "can you feel where on the number line", "start": 164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the solution is likely to fall?", "start": 166.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Or look at the foreign word and the sounds:", "start": 169.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "can you get a sense of the range of meanings", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that it's pointing you towards?", "start": 174.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in terms of the line of poetry,", "start": 177.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "why does the poet use the word hare", "start": 180.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rather than rabbit?", "start": 182.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I'm asking you to do this", "start": 186.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because I believe our personal perceptions, you see,", "start": 188.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "are at the heart", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of how we acquire knowledge.", "start": 194.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Aesthetic judgments,", "start": 196.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rather than abstract reasoning,", "start": 198.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "guide and shape the process", "start": 201.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by which we all come to know", "start": 203.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what we know.", "start": 206.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'm an extreme example of this.", "start": 208.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "My worlds of words and numbers", "start": 211.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "blur with color, emotion", "start": 214.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and personality.", "start": 216.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As Juan said,", "start": 218.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's the condition that scientists call synesthesia,", "start": 220.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "an unusual cross-talk", "start": 223.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between the senses.", "start": 225.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here are the numbers one to 12", "start": 231.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as I see them --", "start": 233.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "every number with its own shape and character.", "start": 235.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "One is a flash of white light.", "start": 239.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Six is a tiny and very sad black hole.", "start": 241.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "The sketches are in black and white here,", "start": 246.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but in my mind they have colors.", "start": 249.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Three is green.", "start": 251.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Four is blue.", "start": 253.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Five is yellow.", "start": 255.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I paint as well.", "start": 260.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And here is one of my paintings.", "start": 262.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a multiplication of two prime numbers.", "start": 265.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Three-dimensional shapes", "start": 269.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the space they create in the middle", "start": 271.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "creates a new shape,", "start": 274.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the answer to the sum.", "start": 276.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What about bigger numbers?", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Well you can't get much bigger than Pi,", "start": 281.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "the mathematical constant.", "start": 285.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's an infinite number --", "start": 287.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "literally goes on forever.", "start": 289.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In this painting that I made", "start": 291.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the first 20 decimals of Pi,", "start": 293.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I take the colors", "start": 297.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the emotions and the textures", "start": 299.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and I pull them all together", "start": 302.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into a kind of rolling numerical landscape.", "start": 304.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "But it's not only numbers that I see in colors.", "start": 309.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Words too, for me,", "start": 312.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have colors and emotions", "start": 314.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and textures.", "start": 316.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this is an opening phrase", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from the novel \"Lolita.\"", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And Nabokov was himself synesthetic.", "start": 322.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And you can see here", "start": 326.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "how my perception of the sound L", "start": 328.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "helps the alliteration", "start": 331.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to jump right out.", "start": 333.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Another example:", "start": 336.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a little bit more mathematical.", "start": 338.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I wonder if some of you will notice", "start": 340.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the construction of the sentence", "start": 342.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from \"The Great Gatsby.\"", "start": 344.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There is a procession of syllables --", "start": 348.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "wheat, one;", "start": 351.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "prairies, two;", "start": 353.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "lost Swede towns, three --", "start": 355.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "one, two, three.", "start": 358.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this effect is very pleasant on the mind,", "start": 360.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and it helps the sentence", "start": 364.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to feel right.", "start": 366.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let's go back to the questions", "start": 369.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I posed you a moment ago.", "start": 371.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "64 multiplied by 75.", "start": 374.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If some of you play chess,", "start": 377.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you'll know that 64", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a square number,", "start": 382.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and that's why chessboards,", "start": 385.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "eight by eight,", "start": 387.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have 64 squares.", "start": 389.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So that gives us a form", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that we can picture, that we can perceive.", "start": 394.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What about 75?", "start": 397.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well if 100,", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we think of 100 as being like a square,", "start": 402.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "75 would look like this.", "start": 405.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what we need to do now", "start": 408.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is put those two pictures", "start": 410.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "together in our mind --", "start": 412.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "something like this.", "start": 414.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "64 becomes 6,400.", "start": 417.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And in the right-hand corner,", "start": 421.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "you don't have to calculate anything.", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Four across, four up and down --", "start": 427.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's 16.", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what the sum is actually asking you to do", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is 16,", "start": 434.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "16, 16.", "start": 436.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's a lot easier", "start": 439.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than the way that the school taught you to do math, I'm sure.", "start": 441.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's 16, 16, 16, 48,", "start": 444.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "4,800 --", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "4,800,", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the answer to the sum.", "start": 450.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Easy when you know how.", "start": 453.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 455.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The second question was an Icelandic word.", "start": 458.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I'm assuming there are not many people here", "start": 461.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who speak Icelandic.", "start": 464.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So let me narrow the choices down to two.", "start": 466.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Hnugginn:", "start": 471.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is it a happy word,", "start": 473.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or a sad word?", "start": 475.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What do you say?", "start": 477.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Okay.", "start": 480.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Some people say it's happy.", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Most people, a majority of people,", "start": 484.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "say sad.", "start": 486.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it actually means sad.", "start": 488.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 492.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Why do, statistically,", "start": 495.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a majority of people", "start": 498.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "say that a word is sad, in this case,", "start": 500.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "heavy in other cases?", "start": 502.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In my theory, language evolves in such a way", "start": 505.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that sounds match,", "start": 508.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "correspond with, the subjective,", "start": 510.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with the personal,", "start": 513.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "intuitive experience", "start": 515.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the listener.", "start": 517.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's have a look at the third question.", "start": 520.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a line from a poem by John Keats.", "start": 524.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Words, like numbers,", "start": 527.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "express fundamental relationships", "start": 530.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between objects", "start": 533.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and events and forces", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that constitute our world.", "start": 537.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It stands to reason that we, existing in this world,", "start": 539.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "should in the course of our lives", "start": 542.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "absorb intuitively those relationships.", "start": 544.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And poets, like other artists,", "start": 547.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "play with those intuitive understandings.", "start": 550.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the case of hare,", "start": 553.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's an ambiguous sound in English.", "start": 556.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It can also mean the fibers that grow from a head.", "start": 558.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And if we think of that --", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "let me put the picture up --", "start": 563.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the fibers represent vulnerability.", "start": 565.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They yield to the slightest movement", "start": 569.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or motion or emotion.", "start": 572.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what you have is an atmosphere", "start": 575.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "of vulnerability and tension.", "start": 579.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The hare itself, the animal --", "start": 581.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not a cat, not a dog, a hare --", "start": 583.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "why a hare?", "start": 586.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because think of the picture --", "start": 588.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not the word, the picture.", "start": 590.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The overlong ears,", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the overlarge feet,", "start": 594.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "helps us to picture, to feel intuitively,", "start": 596.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what it means to limp", "start": 599.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to tremble.", "start": 602.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So in these few minutes,", "start": 605.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I hope I've been able to share", "start": 607.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a little bit of my vision of things", "start": 609.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to show you", "start": 612.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that words can have colors and emotions,", "start": 615.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "numbers, shapes and personalities.", "start": 618.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The world is richer,", "start": 621.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "vaster", "start": 623.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than it too often seems to be.", "start": 625.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I hope that I've given you the desire", "start": 628.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to learn to see the world with new eyes.", "start": 631.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 634.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 636.26, "duration": 11.0}]